main event: On 13 June 1966, a civilian reported a sighting of a stationary object in Morrisonville, New York, observing it for approximately 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object was round, emitting light rays and twinkling like a star.; It was observed from a home 2 miles north of Morrisonville.; The observer was a 44-year-old telephone operator.; The report concluded that the object was likely the planet Saturn due to its size and appearance.; No sound or physical evidence was reported.
sighted object: one round object with a yellowish glow
